#                                          TextMate-grammar team) +
#                                          Anthony Fu (antfu) at the
#                                          shikijs collective; uses VS
#                                          Code's `.tmLanguage.json`
#                                          TextMate grammars + `.tmTheme`
#                                          theme JSONs for pixel-
#                                          identical output to VS Code's
#                                          built-in renderer.  Used by
#                                          Astro, Vue docs, Nuxt docs,
#                                          TypeScript playground, Stack
#                                          Overflow for Teams, and most
#                                          modern static site generators.
#                 → shiki / skat (@shikijs/cli — Pine Wu + Anthony Fu —
#                                  official Shiki CLI offering shiki/
#                                  shiki-cli/skat/@shikijs/cli bin
#                                  aliases; --theme/--lang/--format
#                                  ansi|html/--list-themes/--list-langs
#                                  with file/URL/stdin input;
#                                  13431★ MIT on lib)
#                 _shiki          [TS-Node=235 CLOSES Axis 180, 1/1/1]
#                                                  ↑↑↑ THIS FILE ↑↑↑
#                 shiki is unique among the three lanes in that its
#                 grammars come from VS Code itself — they're the same
#                 `.tmLanguage.json` files Microsoft maintains for the
#                 editor.  No grammar drift between editor and renderer.
#                 chroma uses Pygments grammars (Python ecosystem
#                 heritage); syntect uses Sublime Text grammars
#                 (Sublime ecosystem heritage).  Three different grammar
#                 traditions, all pure-language implementations of
#                 their respective ecosystems' canonical syntax format.
#
# Round-number 235 landmark fires simultaneously across all three lanes:
# Rust completion #235 (_microbin) + Go completion #235 (_fac) + TS-Node
# completion #235 (_shiki) = triple-235.  Axis #173 closed in the
# lifetime of the corpus — every pure-language syntax highlighting
# library in the three big systems languages now has both a
# representative consumer completion AND a documented axis closure
# landmark; the lanes are tied together by a common design discipline
# (pure-host-language lexer + formatter framework reading industry-
# standard grammar files without shelling out to Pygments/highlight.js/
# rouge).
